### Design decisions worth noting

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `try/except` around **every** log call | Satisfies the "must not propagate" guarantee even for edge cases like broken log handler config or format-string mismatches at runtime |
| `_mask_email` / `_mask_cc` as module-level helpers | Centralises masking logic; both are themselves guarded against exceptions so they never cause a log call to fail |
| Email masked at **all** levels, not just DEBUG | The requirement only mandates DEBUG masking, but masking everywhere is strictly safer and there's no stated need to expose the full address at higher levels |
| `SMTP_PASS` **never appears** in any log call | Even as a variable reference; only `SMTP_USER` (the username) is logged during auth |
| Unknown coupon → `WARNING`, not `ERROR` | The original code silently ignores it (valid but unusual), so `WARNING` matches that intent without implying a hard failure |
| Payment failure logged at `ERROR` before `raise` | The exception carries the message upward; the log ensures the failure is recorded even if the caller swallows the exception |
| `_charge_card` / `_charge_paypal` / `_send_email` get their own entry/exit logs | Gives full call-graph visibility in production log streams without any changes to call sites |
